The originality, the story, the overall feeling of this game
GLaDOS fight
The core portal mechanic was mind-bending at the time, both in terms of its interestingness for puzzles but also from a technical perspective (it was like a feat of magic). The story and humour was also especially good.
Portal mechanic itself executed perfectly
I think portal 1 is a perfect example of having a single interesting idea and executing it perfectly. I think it really is telling that it still stands on it own as a fun game to play despite being almost 20 years old. The core mechanic is simple and easy to understand but can be applied to very complex puzzles without becoming over bearing. You can hand portal to someone who doesn’t really play video games and they can probably navigate their way through it with ease.
The strategy and the escape sequence
How it doesn't have any weak spots, It's small and everything is used accordingly. I also like the atmosphere.
The puzzles are very well though regarding the gravity
The mystery surrounding who you were, why you were there, what happened to everyone, really was begging for a sequel (which we got an amazing one) and pulled a lot of intrigue on top of puzzle solving.
The story and puzzle elements
The smooth transition of difficulty in the puzzles
Atmosphere, evolving gameplay that always involves portals.
I really like the puzzles
Solving tests 👍
The eerie-ness of the environment. The atmosphere was very well-crafted.
